<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by HadekkinK on 05-30-2002 01:51 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Re: the solo spot in Acrylia Caverns...

I thought I'd share my experiences here, in case it helps anyone.  60 cleric with BAoTR, no FT gear.

Invis potion gets me all the way from zonein to the camp spot.  I sit in the "far right" corner of that room, basically underneath the High Priests "sacrificing" ledge.  This spot is completely safe - no wanderers, no adds when I pull.  Not sure if this is due to my level but I've never had an add.

About 10 Epitaph of Lifes kills the skeletons.  Max hit from them is about 130, they open with an approx. 500 pt Harm Touch however and try cast a few SK debuffs, no big deal.

The exp is very nice.  It's about on par what I see solo druids and shamans, even warriors / rangers, getting in FG / the Grey and other places.  However, getting this exp as a cleric is a welcome change.  Shamans and others may do better soloing in their normal spots, but if you have some type of mana regen, and are high enough level to single pull, I'd have to say this spot is agreeable to cleric soloing.

Few bits of advice:

1.  Have Gate up, and be Aegoed / BAoTR at all times.  If your invis fades otw to the camp...well, it'll pretty much suck  :(.  There are some mobs that see invis otw to the camp, namely the possessed priests (look like piles of bones on the ground) however if you're careful / clever you can manuever your way past them.  I'm not sure if someone of lower level with corresponding larger aggro radius would have the same success, as you do need to get quite close to one or two of them otw to the camp spot.

2.  Be aware of the pathing.  If you sit too close to the wall, the skeletons will do one of two things, depending on their level of hit points:

A.  Freeze in place.  This is not only cheating, it's probably a suspendable offense if a guide catches you exploiting it.  The guide I brought this up to last night gave me the go ahead to camp here, just mentioned that I shouldn't try to use this to my advantage.  No problem.

B.  If the skeleton is low on hps, and you get close enough to the wall to freeze up it's pathing, many times it will take off running into the lava pool.  What this means for adds / possible trains I didn't waste time to find out, was too busy Gating  :).

So just be aware of that possible problem...

Respawn time is 15 mins, give or take.  With a lot of chatting and with my sucky gear, I could really only keep 3 of the skels cleared before respawn.  Given the number of skels all around (some in High Priest room, some in red gems room, some in jail room?) this spot could probably support 2, maybe even 3 soloers.  So be nice and share  :).

Once again exp isn't totally out of whack, and there is some risk, but if you can't find a group check this out.
</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
